Definition: the person who gives a mortgage in return for money to be repaid
Example: we became mortgagors when the bank accepted our mortgage and loaned us the money to buy our new home
Synonyms: verb, possession, mortgage, mortgager, debtor, the, person, who, gives, a, in, return, for, money, to, be, repaid, we, became, mortgagors, when, bank, accepted, our, and, loaned, us, buy, new, home
Category: noun.person
